author: Mike Santa Barbara
title: Jags fall to defending champs William Penn, 48-6
text: Jags fall to defending champs William Penn, 48-6 Comment By Mike Santa Barbara Posted Oct. 10, 2015 @ 4:24 pm The Appoquinimink Jaguars fell to 2-3 on the season, falling to defending Division I State Champions William Penn on Saturday, 48-6. The Jags kept it close against the Colonials in the first quarter, trailing just 13-6. Though, William Penn turned up the pressure leading into the half scoring twice in the second quarter to take a commanding 27-6 lead at the break. Appo had no answers for the electric William Penn offense in the second half as the Colonials tacked on 21 more points in the half to win going away, 48-6. The Jags are back in action next week hosting Charter School of Wilmington (1-4) Friday night at 7 p.m.
